---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const title = "About Us";
const description = "Learn about the mission, calculations, and engineering goals of HomeProjectHub.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto flex flex-col gap-6 py-4">
    <header class="border-b border-neutral-150 dark:border-neutral-800 pb-6 mb-2">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-50 mb-2">
        About HomeProjectHub
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-450 leading-relaxed text-pretty">
        Empowering homeowners and DIYers with transparent, mathematically rigorous planning tools.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed text-pretty">
      <p>
        HomeProjectHub was founded to bridge the gap between complex engineering calculations and everyday home improvement projects. When planning a renovation, backyard project, or major construction pour, getting the material quantities correct is the difference between a successful project and an expensive headache.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-800 dark:text-neutral-250 mt-4">
        Our Core Philosophy
      </h2>
      <p>
        We believe that planning calculators shouldn't just be black boxes that output a single number. To help build real homeowner expertise (E-E-A-T), we are committed to:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 flex flex-col gap-2">
        <li><strong>Open Math Formulas:</strong> Every single calculator on our platform outlines the exact arithmetic, geometry, and material weight equations used.</li>
        <li><strong>Worked Examples:</strong> We provide real-world worked scenarios so you can double check the math yourself using a pen and paper.</li>
        <li><strong>Structural Nuance:</strong> We highlight common construction mistakes (like soil compaction and formwork flexing) that simple calculators ignore, preventing you from running short on materials.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-800 dark:text-neutral-250 mt-4">
        Our Engineering Principles
      </h2>
      <p>
        HomeProjectHub is built using modern static web technology (Astro and Tailwind CSS v4) to ensure it is lightning-fast, uses zero tracking cookies by default, and maintains 100/100 Core Web Vitals. Your private room data is stored entirely locally on your own machine.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
